Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
write_ml_timing_graph(25.10)                      write_ml_timing_graph(25.10)

Name
       write_ml_timing_graph  -  Writes  timing-related  data for JedAI to csv
       files

Syntax
       write_ml_timing_graph

       [-help]

        [-noedge]

       -prefix <string>

       [-register_only]

        [-views <view_list>]

       Writes timing-related data for JedAI to csv  files.  It  includes  data
       representing  the  complete  timing  graph  for a given set of analysis
       views.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes the  type  and  default
              information for each write_ml_timing_graph parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command

              man write_ml_timing_graph.

       -noedge
              Specifies  that  edge data should not be dumped. This option can
              be used to save time.

              Data_type: int, optional

       -prefix <string>
              Specifies the prefix for the output files.

              Data_type: string, required

       -register_only
              Specifies that only nodes for register should be dumped.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -views <view_list>
              Dumps the data for the specified analysis view(s).

              Data_type: tcl_obj, optional

Example
              * The following command writes the timing-related data for JedAI
                to csv files with the specified prefix:

                write_ml_timing_graph -prefix out/

Related Information
              * init_ml

              * write_ml_design

              * write_ml_library

              * write_ml_timing_path

